Buses replace trains this weekend

Work is taking place to maintain and upgrade the rail network this weekend. Saturday 27 and Sunday 28 May buses will replace trains on the: 
 • Eastern Line – Buses replace trains between Britomart and Manukau.
 • Southern Line – Buses replace trains between Papakura and Ōtāhuhu.

Additionally, on Sunday buses will replace trains between Newmarket and Britomart after 10:30pm. This includes the last train towards Britomart on each of the Western and Onehunga Lines, and the last train each way on the Southern Line.

Rail bus services are shown in the Journey Planner as bus services, and will have codes RBS, RBO, RBE and RBW.
